.terraform/
.terraform.lock.hcl
.terraform.tfstate.lock.info
*.tfstate.backup

# UNLIKE infra/eks: terraform.tfstate is NOT ignored here.
# Bootstrap's state is tiny (one bucket + block config) and
# committing it means anyone can `tofu destroy` the state
# bucket later without hunting down the original applier's
# laptop. The state bucket is itself a one-per-account
# fixture, not a per-deployment resource.
#
# No secrets in this state — it's just a bucket name and ARN.
